54.4	John_Doerr	John Doerr	L. John Doerr (born June 29, 1951 in St. Louis, Missouri) is an American venture capitalist at Kleiner Perkins Caufield &amp; Byers in Menlo Park, California, in Silicon Valley. In February 2009, Doerr was appointed as a member of the President's Economic Recovery Advisory Board to provide the president and his administration with advice and counsel in fixing America's economic downturn. Forbes ranks Doerr as the 540th richest person in the world, with a net worth of US $2.2 billion.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/John_Doerr.jpg/220px-John_Doerr.jpg
